The paper proposes a new method for learning a similarity function to predict hyperlink weights among data vectors in a hyper-relational dataset. This involves using Bregman divergence and encompasses various existing methods such as logistic regression, Poisson regression, graph embedding, matrix factorization, and tensor factorization. The paper also discusses the robustness of the proposed method against distributional misspecification and its computational tractability. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes a new learning method. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper deals with hyper-relational data and similarity functions. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible sub-categories as the paper discusses the computational tractability of the proposed method and presents a theoretical guarantee for the optimization.
